# ============================================================================
# What TO Commit (Explicitly Listed for Clarity)
# ============================================================================

# ✅ Source code (.py, .ts, .tsx, .js, .jsx)
# ✅ Configuration files (package.json, requirements.txt, tsconfig.json)
# ✅ Docker config (docker-compose.yml, Dockerfile)
# ✅ Database migrations (alembic/versions/*.py)
# ✅ Documentation (docs/*.md, README.md)
# ✅ Tests (tests/*.py, __tests__/*.ts)
# ✅ .gitignore (this file!)
# ✅ VS Code shared settings (.vscode/settings.json)

# ============================================================================
# Notes on Security
# ============================================================================

# NEVER commit:
# - Passwords
# - API keys
# - Database credentials
# - Access tokens
# - Private keys
# - .env files

# If you accidentally commit a secret:
# 1. Remove it from git history (git filter-branch or BFG Repo Cleaner)
# 2. Rotate the secret immediately (change password, regenerate API key)
# 3. Pushing to GitHub with secrets triggers security alerts
